Eskom CEO André de Ruyter said the ongoing outages are necessary to catch up with long overdue maintenance. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom CEO Andre De Ruyter says they had no alternative but to implement load-shedding. He says the power utility has depleted its emergency reserves and will use the downtime to replenish stock. READ: Eskom COO apologises for power cuts "We obviously regret this and we are working hard to bring units back as quickly as possible and we are hoping to reduce the extent of load-shedding as much as we can but in this instance unfortunately we had no alternative but to implement this decision," he said. Eskom implemented stage 2 power cuts from Wednesday until Monday morning.